&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Staff Nurse (Pre–op Assessment) - Full Time and Part Time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pre-op Assessment at the Royal Berkshire Hospital is undergoing exciting changes and we need pro-active, driven nurses to join the team to support these changes. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Currently Pre-Operative assessment is open from 07.45 to 18.15 Monday to Friday and 08:00 to 13.00 on Saturdays.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Pre-op assessment focuses on optimizing patients for planned surgery and enhancing the patient experience. You will need to have excellent communication skills and be keen to develop your patient assessment, decision making and clinical skills.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We offer flexible working through the self-rostering system and provide opportunities for nurses to develop both professionally and personally, through local training and external professional courses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sue Hatch (Sister) on 0118 322 8532 or susan.hatch@royalberkshire.nhs.uk or Claire Vincent (Senior Staff Nurse) on 0118 322 8515 or claire.vincent@royalberkshire.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
